well for context, catholic confirmation is technically the renewal of your baptismal vows now that you're considered an adult by the church (your parents & god parents did it "for you" when you were a baby), so you just have a special mass with other confirmation candidates where you wear basically a graduation gown, say some prayers, then go up and get confirmed by the bishop where you tell them the saint whose name you chose; then a bar/bat mitzvah is similar but different, it's a single person close to their birthday and there's a service where they read from the Torah on their own etc, and then you have a big party afterward (a party is optional for confirmation, like my best friend had a little reception but I didn't)
